g.text: Loads to Cloud BigQuery and performs Query Analytics
Notidy via Slack / Email as an example
** GREEN here means these initial cloud functions have been implemented, development is in progress...for remaining; system design is subject to change
RED Text And GREEN Stoke boxes means partially completed in progress
Analytics triggered by a Submit of Interest Request
* This appends a row in BigQuery for Interest Request
Submitted. There is also env variable for query only mode
to bypass this fpr development mode.
* Based on the interest request submitted, this does query on BigQuery
for delta calculations overall for last 5 requests to
compare the delta calculations. This result is placed in Analytics struct
* Then it also Publishes as JSON the analytics message to PubSub.
Currently, adds logs to console log explorer
from base64 encoding per JSON message schema received
